-- 
Czech Airlines to Open Bratislava Hub With Six Routes, SME Says

-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 
2011-05-13T07:14:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/czech-airlines-to-open-bratislava-hub-with-six-routes-sme-says.html
Czech Airlines will open a base in
Bratislava, the capital of neighboring Slovakia, offering six
routes in addition to the existing Prague-Bratislava service,
 SME  reported.  The Czech carrier will serve Amsterdam, Barcelona,
Brussels, Larnaka, Paris and  Rome  from Bratislava, the newspaper
said, citing Dana Madunicka, a Bratislava airport spokeswoman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 